Yes, music can be fun and enjoyable. In JavaScript, you can describe the fun aspect of music by creating a simple program that plays a song when a button is clicked. Here's an example:

```javascript
// Create an audio element
const audio = new Audio('path/to/your/song.mp3');

// Get the button element
const button = document.getElementById('play-button');

// Function to play the song when button is clicked
function playSong() {
  audio.play();
}

// Attach the playSong function to the button's click event
button.addEventListener('click', playSong);
```

In the above code, you first create an `Audio` element and provide the path to your desired song. Then, you retrieve the button element using `getElementById` function. Finally, you define a function `playSong` that plays the audio when called and attach this function to the button's click event using `addEventListener`. 

By executing this code, whenever you click the button with the id 'play-button', the song will start playing, ensuring a fun and enjoyable experience with music in JavaScript!
